		},
		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "Domain E , considered as the putative hormone binding domain ( HBD ) of the human mineralocorticoid receptor ( hMR ) was expressed in Escherichia coli as a fusion protein with either maltose binding protein ( MBP ) or glutathione S-transferase ( GST ) . <S>",
			"relation": "ROOT",
			"tag": "Verification-Method"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "These bacterially-produced MR constructs had no steroid binding activity per se . <S>",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "In fact , heat shock protein association ( hsp ) is required for high affinity ligand-binding of the MR . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "After incubation of purified MBP- or GST-HBD with rabbit reticulocyte lysate , known to be rich in heat shock proteins , we obtained saturable binding of [3H]aldosterone . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "The Kd value for aldosterone was 0.3 nM and the Bmax = 32 pmol/mg . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "Hormone binding specificity was assessed by competition studies with various steroid ligands . <S>",
			"relation": "MANNER-MEANS",
			"tag": "Verification-Method"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "Sucrose gradient assays performed with [3H]aldosterone-MBP-HBD revealed complex sedimenting at 8.3S and 4.9S with [3H]progesterone-MBP-HBD . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "Western-blot analysis of the sedimentation peak showed the concomitant presence of MBP-HBD by a monoclonal anti-MBP antibody , and hsp90 by a monoclonal anti-hsp antibody . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "Moreover ,",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "following incubation with the anti-rabbit hsp90 monoclonal antibody",
			"relation": "TEMPORAL",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "the sedimenting gradient showed a 10.4S sedimenting complex . <S>",
			"relation": "SAME-UNIT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "These analyses demonstrated",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "that the [3H]aldosterone-MBP-HBD complex is at least associated with hsp90 in reticulocyte lysate",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "and that the HBD of hMR is sufficient to bind hsp90 . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "Deletions of a relatively short amino- ( 729-766 ) or carboxy- terminal ( 940-984 ) region of the HBD fragment eliminated all steroid-binding properties . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 16,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "Overall , these results indicate",
			"relation": "CONCLUSION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		},
		{
			"id": 17,
			"parent": 16,
			"text": "that the integrity of domain E is necessary and sufficient to bind steroid ligands , agonists or antagonists , with characteristics similar to the entire native MR . <S>",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		}
	]
}